sentences: Roman Kostrzewski (born 15 February 1960) is a Polish heavy metal musician.
He was the lead vocalist and songwriter of Kat until 2005.
He also founded Alkatraz, another heavy metal band, with Valdi Moder in 2000.
In 1984 KAT was considered the favourite act at Jarocin festival.
In 1985 KAT released their debut album 666 and its English version Metal and Hell.
The first day after release was an immense success where they played at Jarocin festival (the band sold over 4000 copies).
